properties.areaDesc: West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 7 at 3:32AM PST until January 8 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected above 3000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of up to 12 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Darrington, Index, Skykomish, Stevens
Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 4 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Rain or rain/snow mix will be possible
through most of Tuesday ahead of a cold front. Later this
evening, rain will transition back to snow as colder air moves
in, with snow levels dropping down to 2500-3500 feet. The
Northwest Avalanche Center expects high avalanche danger to
continue through Tuesday with dangerous conditions through
Wednesday. Check nwac.us for the latest avalanche conditions
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 4 AM PST WEDNESDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
